(1059, 290, 'panels_data', 'a:3:{s:7:"widgets";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:4:"text";s:773:"<h1>Personal Timeline</h1><h1><img class="wp-image-281 aligncenter" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png" alt="" width="761" height="259" /></h1><h2>Life in Dubai </h2><p>Born in the Newyork of the Middle East, I grew up in a multicultural environement that encouraged innovation. The highrises I would wake up to were, to me, a testament and a reminder of the capacities of the human intellect and the power of human ambition. The large scale projects, the grand expos and the bussing steets voiced the innovative spirit that Dubai, and consequently I, had. </p><p><img class="alignnone wp-image-287" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png" width="1003" height="194" /></p>";s:20:"text_selected_editor";s:7:"tinymce";s:5:"autop";b:1;s:12:"_sow_form_id";s:13:"587ddda2ce3f8";s:11:"panels_info";a:6:{s:5:"class";s:31:"SiteOrigin_Widget_Editor_Widget";s:4:"grid";i:0;s:4:"cell";i:0;s:2:"id";i:0;s:9:"widget_id";s:36:"8472d5d1-3250-4a82-8b46-d59a437c6792";s:5:"style";a:3:{s:27:"background_image_attachment";b:0;s:18:"background_display";s:4:"tile";s:10:"font_color";s:7:"#3f83bf";}}}}s:5:"grids";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:"cells";i:1;s:5:"style";a:0:{}}}s:10:"grid_cells";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:"grid";i:0;s:6:"weight";i:1;}}}'),
