(256, 1, '2017-01-17 08:42:37', '2017-01-17 08:42:37', '<h1 style="color: #0099cc;">Personal Timeline</h1>\r\n<h1><img class="wp-image-281 aligncenter" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png" sizes="(max-width: 761px) 100vw, 761px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-768x262.png 768w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2.png 984w" alt="" width="761" height="259"></h1>\r\n<h2>Life in Dubai</h2>\r\n<p>Born in the New York of the Middle East, I grew up in a multicultural environnement that encouraged innovation. The high-rises I would wake up to were, to me, a testament and a reminder of the capacities of the human intellect and the power of human ambition. The large scale projects, the&nbsp;grand expos and the busing streets voiced the innovative spirit that Dubai, and consequently I, had. My family and I left Dubai in 2009 following the 2008 recession.<br>\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-287" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png" sizes="(max-width: 1003px) 100vw, 1003px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-1024x197.png 1024w" width="1003" height="194"></p>\r\n<h2>Life in Tunisia</h2>\r\n<p>Far the busy five-laned roads and the sky piercing buildings, the city of Sousse is a quiet and costal city in Tunisia. The quiet however did not remain for long. A year after I moved to Sousse the Tunisian Revolution, nicknamed the "Revolution of the Jasmines", broke out. I witnessed the protests, heard the gunfire and participated in protecting our neighborhood.</p>\r\n<p>Neither my studies nor my moral were hindered due to the move and the subsequent revolution. On the contrary they were strengthened.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-296" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r-300x160.png" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r-300x160.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r.png 425w" alt="" width="300" height="160"></p>\r\n<h2>Life in&nbsp;Egypt</h2>\r\n<p>Despite having lived in and visited Egypt, I did not know much of what Egypt has to offer. Gaining acceptance to AUC triggered a process of discovering what I hitherto considered familiar. Underneath the political turmoil and economic instability is a thriving and diverse population that calls for unity and prosperity. I am still uncovering the secrets of Egypt. Who knows what I will discover?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<a class="ow-button-hover" href="http://localhost/wp/education/">\r\n<span>\r\n<span class="sow-icon-fontawesome" data-sow-icon="" style="color: #000000"></span>\r\nTo Education		</span>\r\n</a>', 'Background', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'background', '', '', '2017-01-17 15:21:11', '2017-01-17 15:21:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wp/?page_id=256', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(257, 1, '2017-01-17 08:42:37', '2017-01-17 08:42:37', '<h2 style="color: #0099cc;">Work experience</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Digital Innovation: Consultant (intern).</li>\r\n<li>ESL teacher</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style="color: #0099cc;">Extracurricular activities:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>American corner: assistant and member :</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The American Corner in Sousse is an independent English language library and cultural center geared for sharing information about the United States, foreign exchange program opportunities, improving language fluency and organizing activities and events.<br>\r\nMy role in this organization included but was not limited to:<br>\r\n*Hosting, organizing and advertising social events such as : monthly coffee house( Art talent show ), Guest speakers( community leaders, entrepreneurs, change makers, officials...), environmental acts( cleanups and campaigns )<br>\r\n*Managing, founding and leading clubs: Media club, Drama club,book club...<br>\r\n*Conducting workshops: programming, soft skill development, creative writing...<br>\r\n*Welcoming guests and advertising the organization<br>\r\n*General library work( supervising, book inventory, IT support...)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>AUC Times: Writer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Wrote 3 articles in the monthly main issues and 1 article in the special issue:</p>\r\n<p>Ramadan Is Dead - We are the heroes of our time - All Hail President Trump - One Outlet, Two Revolutions</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Developers Club: Junior self-development trainer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Nautical Club of Sousse: Licensed Rower</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a class="ow-button-hover"></a></p><a class="ow-button-hover">\r\n</a><p><a class="ow-button-hover"></a></p>\r\n<a class="ow-button-hover" href="http://localhost/wp/achievements-and-awards/">\r\n<span>\r\n<span class="sow-icon-icomoon" data-sow-icon=""></span>\r\nTo Skills &amp; Achievements 		</span>\r\n</a>', 'Work and Extraculicular', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'work-and-extraculicular', '', '', '2017-01-17 15:30:25', '2017-01-17 15:30:25', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wp/?page_id=257', 0, 'page', '', 0),
