(288, 1, '2017-01-17 09:14:44', '2017-01-17 09:14:44', '<h1>Personal Timeline</h1>\r\n<h1><img class="wp-image-281 aligncenter" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png" alt="" width="761" height="259" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-768x262.png 768w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2.png 984w" sizes="(max-width: 761px) 100vw, 761px"></h1>\r\n<h2>Life in Dubai&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>Born in the Newyork of the Middle East, I grew up in a multicultural environement that encouraged innovation. The highrises I would wake up to were, to me, a testament and a reminder of the capacities of the human intellect and the power of human ambition. The large scale projects, the&nbsp;grand expos and the bussing steets voiced the innovative spirit that Dubai, and consequently I, had.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone wp-image-287" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png" width="1003" height="194" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-1024x197.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1003px) 100vw, 1003px"></p>', 'Background', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '256-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-17 09:14:44', '2017-01-17 09:14:44', '', 256, 'http://localhost/wp/2017/01/17/256-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(290, 1, '2017-01-17 09:17:18', '2017-01-17 09:17:18', '<h1>Personal Timeline</h1><h1><img class="wp-image-281 aligncenter" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png" alt="" width="761" height="259" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-768x262.png 768w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2.png 984w" sizes="(max-width: 761px) 100vw, 761px"></h1><h2>Life in Dubai&nbsp;</h2>Born in the Newyork of the Middle East, I grew up in a multicultural environement that encouraged innovation. The highrises I would wake up to were, to me, a testament and a reminder of the capacities of the human intellect and the power of human ambition. The large scale projects, the&nbsp;grand expos and the bussing steets voiced the innovative spirit that Dubai, and consequently I, had.&nbsp;\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-287" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png" width="1003" height="194" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-1024x197.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1003px) 100vw, 1003px">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Life in Tunisia&nbsp;</h2>&nbsp;', 'Background', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '256-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-17 09:17:18', '2017-01-17 09:17:18', '', 256, 'http://localhost/wp/2017/01/17/256-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
